<title type="html"><![CDATA[6/11(Thu.) The smell of coffee/ Should we have a bucket list? (Host: Morris)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=398&amp;p=415#p415"><![CDATA[
Session I: The smell of coffee<br /><br />Please watch the following video to learn about “the smell of coffee” from BBC 6 minute English:<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5R3WdBE1-JM">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5R3WdBE1-JM</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions:<br />1.If you watched the video, please share what you learned from it, such as new ideas, vocabularies, and phrases? <br /><br />2.Do you like drinking coffee? If yes, how do you make it, by purchasing it from a shop, or brewing it by yourself? If you don’t like coffee, what other kind of beverage do you like? And why?<br /><br />3.Do you think the “the smell of coffee” is important? What make  good coffee(or the beverage you like) to you?<br /><br />4.What does it mean to have “good taste”? Drinking Starbucks coffee means having better taste than having 7-11 coffee? Or using iPhone instead of other brands? Going to see an opera instead of a rap/hip hop concert? Collecting real artworks instead of IKEA paintings? Wearing Prada instead of NET?   What does it mean when someone says someone has good taste?<br /><br /><br /><br />Session II: Should we have a bucket list?<br />Please watch the following video to learn about “Should we have a bucket list?” from BBC 6 minute English:<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Nb7wVCJ68YY">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Nb7wVCJ68YY</a><!-- m --><br /><br /><br />Questions:<br />1.If you watched the video, please share what you learned from it, such as new ideas, vocabularies, and phrases?<br /><br />2.What are the pros and cons to have a bucket list?<br /><br />3.Are you a spontaneous or organized person?  What reasons made you such kind of person? Do you like yourself now? Why or why not?<br /><br />4.Do you have a bucket list? If yes, what are the items on your list and how many of them have been completed? If no, do you have any goals in your life?<br /><br />Agenda<br />7:00 pm-7:30 pm Free talk<br />7:30 pm-8:10 pm Session 1 discussion<br />8:10 pm-8:40 pm Presentation (At least two members of each table are invited)<br />8:40 pm-8:45 pm Break time &amp; Group picture<br />8:45 pm-9:15 pm Session 2 discussion<br />9:15 pm-9:30 pm Presentation<br /><br />The meeting place of Thursday:<br />怡客咖啡, 台北市衡陽路116號<br />捷運資訊： 近台北捷運–西門站<br />怡客低消: NT$80元<br />最自由的全英文會話聚會，前三次不用交會費，加入會員終生會費NT$500，帶著開放與熱情來學英文。<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=13721">morris</a> — Fri Jun 05, 2020 9:31 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
